<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-05-04T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-05-04T03:00:00-05:00" n="669" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d669">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.6363/54: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Child</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Genoa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-04T09:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 4, 1922—9
                                        a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received May 4—5:57
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>22. Your telegram of May 2, 5 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>] p.m. I have a
                            categorical denial from Worthington-Evans<note n="16" xml:id="d669fn16">Sir Laming Worthington-Evans, member of the British
                                delegation.</note> that the supposed Krassin, Boyle, Dutch-Shell
                            agreement has been signed. Evans states that the information would have
                            been given to his delegation if it were true. In answer to an inquirer
                            the Russian delegation has replied that while negotiations have been
                            taking place a conclusion has not been reached.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Child</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>